FBIS4-13176 "drnes074_r_94001" FBIS-NES-94-074 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 India Officials, Parties React to Signing of GATT Accord Officials, Parties React to Signing of GATT Accord Congress-I Welcomes Signing BK1504162694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 15 Apr 94 BK1504162694 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The Congress-I has welcomed the signing of the new GATT accord by India at Marrakech and charged the opposition with indulging in a disinformation campaign on the issue. Speaking to reporters in New Delhi today, the party spokesman, Mr. V.N. Gadgil, said the agreement will boost India's agricultural and textile exports. He said the government will now have to translate the agreement into various laws and these have to come before parliament. The minister of state for commerce, Mr. Kamaluddin Ahmad, said that the new agreement is on the whole beneficial to India. Speaking to a group of foreign journalists in New Delhi today, he reaffirmed India's faith in a rule-based transparent multilateral trading system. The BJP [Bharatiya Janata Party] president, Mr. L.K. Advani, has criticized the signing of the Marrakech Declaration by India. He said in New Delhi that the treaty has been conceived by developed countries to promote their trade interests.
